title: Suoni delle Dolomiti - Carminho
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - The poignant poetry of fado interpreted by an extraordinary voice. The 2024 edition of I Suoni delle Dolomiti will get underway at Malga Tassulla, with a voice that embodies the spirit and poetry of fado, Portugal's quintessential music genre: the location is in the natural amphitheater wrapped around the Pian della Nana, in the northernmost and most mysterious part of the Brenta Dolomites, where silence forms the soundtrack for hikers.
Carminho is one of the most talented and innovative fado singers of her generation. She followed in the footsteps of her mother di lei – another famous fado artist – and is very familiar with the tradition, but during her career di lei she has also made forays into Brazilian music, jazz and pop. Entitled Portuguesa, the most recent of her six albums by her is almost a declaration of her intent to strike a balance between the traditional and the modern in her songs and the music of her homeland. “The genesis of Portuguesa has the same basis as my previous albums: the irresistible fascination of fado, which for me is a language more than a message, a path more than a destination,” states Carminho.

title: Charta della Regola
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - Cavareno opens its doors to the Charta della Regola celebration, the spectacular historical re-enactment of the ancient municipal regulations.
For the occasion, the town is transformed into a real medieval village, to remember the period of the Charter of the Rule, the ancient statute that established the rules of peasant life, from cutting hay to social organisation.
The event therefore aims to revive the atmosphere of the peasant life of the past and to raise awareness of ancient crafts.
The streets and streets of the village will be full of artisans, farmers, nobles and commoners, but in addition to the parades in period costume and the usual reading of the document, there will be food and wine stands, cultural events, activities for children, music and there will be possibility of visiting the churches and historic buildings of the village.
